post_text:
8th Grade Graduation Announcement

Please spread the word that we are wanting the communities of Oglesby Public Schools to be as loud as a 737 airplane to support our recent graduates! Tell your friends, family and Facebook feed to get outside and give a thunderous round of applause tomorrow, Thursday, May 28th, at 7:37 p.m., in honor of the 8th grade graduates of Oglesby Washington School!

An 8th grade graduation video will be published on the school's website and that link will be sent out via text and email tomorrow afternoon so that families can prepare to watch it at 7:00 p.m. with their family and graduates!

Congratulations to the Washington Junior High Class of 2020!

post_text: The Scholastic Bowl Team had a match against Marquette Academy in Ottawa on Feb. 13. The A team gave a great effort with scoring 130 points. Greyson won the most toss ups by earning our team over 60 points! Ultimately, the A team lost to Marquette's A Team by 50 points. The B Team had a close match by winning in overtime by a tie-breaker bonus round. Natalie G. won the toss up which helped our team win 105 points to 95 points. 6th Grader, Cole K., received the most toss ups for the B team, earning over 30 points! Great job!

The B Team had a close match by winning in overtime by a tie-breaker bonus round.
